 holy scriptures. At the same time, he proposes a fresh interpretative framework and a new data set for theorizing the early history of Islam, isolating the contradictions between Shi'ite and Sunni sources and their contribution to the tensions that rile these groups today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHadith (Shiites)xCriticism, interpretation, etc. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Koran & Sacred Writings.2bisacsh1 aAmir-Moezzi, Mohammad Ali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnsari, Hasan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKohlberg, Etan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrmsby, Eric.40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/amir1737840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231540650423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231540650.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK